sentences: Karl Appela better known as Blacko, also known as Afrikaf, Tikaf Lakour, Solitary Lion and Black Renega (born in Montfermeil, (Seine-Saint-Denis, France on 5 February 1979) is a French singer and hip hop artist of Réunion origin.
He was member of the hip hop group Sniper from 1997 until his departure in July 2007.
He was member of the hip hop group Sniper from 1997 until his departure in July 2007.
Moving to Deuil-la-Barre in 1995, he was associated with the A.R. Possee group and later at 15, Kaotik.
In 1997, he became part of the hip hop group Sniper with musical event FrancoFolies in La Rochelle.
DJ Boudj left after the initial two albums, Du rire aux larmes (2001) and Gravé dans la roche (2003).
DJ Boudj left after the initial two albums, Du rire aux larmes (2001) and Gravé dans la roche (2003).
With Dj Boudj leaving, the remaining trio had two more albums Trait pour trait and À toute épreuve in 2006.
A final tour in 2007 would mark the end of Sniper.
Even prior to break-off in 2005, he had success with a joint work with 113 in "Un jour de paix".
Immediately upon break-off of Sniper in 2007, he was featured in French rapper Soprano's hit "Ferme les yeux et imagine toi".
In 2009, his first solo reggae album Enfant du soleil halted with the Desh Musique label refusing its release.
Instead Blacko took part in Kool Shen's 2009 album Eldorado.
In 2010, he released his 17 track album Enfant du soleil independently online, explaining his fall-off with Desh Musique and his musical orientation for ragga and reggae.

End of 2011, he released an EP of 5 title under the title Instin Kaf made available for free downloads.
In 2014, his single "Le temps est compté" has charted on SNEP, the official French singles chart.
